cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.FL, cs.SY. 

The paper deals with the reachability analysis of recursive programs that communicate asynchronously over reliable FIFO channels. This involves the study of pushdown systems, which are a type of formal language model. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.PL (Programming Languages) are likely sub-categories. The paper also involves the analysis of communication topologies, which can be modeled as graphs, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible sub-category. The use of formal methods and automata theory suggests cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) as another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the analysis of systems, which can be modeled as control systems, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible sub-category.
